speechtext:
Mr. Speaker, I believe that you will find consent for the following motion:
That, notwithstanding any Standing Order of this House, on Wednesday, March 11, 1992 immediately after the final vote on ways and means Motion No. 11, the House shall proceed to a special debate on the situation now facing the softwood lumber industry;
Routine Proceedings
That, for the sole purpose of this special debate the question before the House shall be that this House do now adjourn;
That, under the provisions of this order, no member shall be permitted to speak more than once;
That, the first three speakers be permitted to speak for 20 minutes and that all speeches thereafter be no longer than 10 minutes;
That, under the provisions of this order, the Speaker shall not entertain any dilatory or superseding motions or quorum calls; and
That, when no member rises to speak, but no later than 12 midnight, the Speaker shall adjourn the House until the next sitting day.
